RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 1 330 Y Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Purse 6300. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ABSOLUTION BY FIRE driving, drifted out. THREATLEVELMIDNIGHT big late run. J BEST QUEEN veered in, bothered foe. DG VICTORYNVALHALLA bumped hard, forced in. FELL OFF THE WAGON foe crossed path late. A MINI SECRET solid effort, out kicked. MY BABY clean trip. JESS DOWN THE RAPIDS broke in sharply, bothered foe. DG TIME FOR IVORY bumped had, forced in. IVYCANTOO pinched back start. STEWARD INQUIRY WAS POSTED INTO THE RUNNING NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE, JOCKEY OBJECTION WAS ALSO LODGED, JOCKEY OF DG VICTORYNVALHALLA AND THE JOCKEY OF JESS DOWN THE RAPIDS CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE JOCKEY OF J BEST QUEEN FOR INTERFERENCE NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE, AFTER A REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS ALLOWED AND J BEST QUEEN WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM THIRD TO TENTH AND THE INQUIRY DISQUALIFIED JESS DOWN THE RAPIDS FROM EIGHTH TO NINTH BOTH FOR INTERFERENCE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 6000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF THREE RACES LIFETIME OR COLORADO BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; , 124 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FROGGY went to the front to a clear lead and set all the pace, was challenged at the top of the stretch, dug in and drew off. OH SNAP trailed the field early, then moved up from three wide and made a late run in the stretch to be a clear second. HOT LIL MESS pressed the pace through the turn then engaged the leader at the top of the stretch and tired. BULL RING steadied coming onto the main track, saved ground throughout but failed to menace. MORE ACTION was off the pace to the four and a half furlong marked then was shuffled back, made a late effort in the stretch and missed the show.

ENTRY.NAME: Bull Ring
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied early, saved ground, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Froggy
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear lead, set pace, dug in, drew off,

ENTRY.NAME: More Action
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, shuffled back, late effort, missed show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 6400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR COLORADO BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCE OTTO was hustled along to vied for the lead then took over at the quarter pole, drew off in mid stretch and held off late closer. BORN TO RACE trailed to the turn then moved up on the turn and angled out to four wide in upper stretch for a late rally but was too late and to prove second best. DEACON BEACON was rushed up the rail to be off the pace but ran into traffic entering the turn and had to check, made a rebid and was up for show. CASH EXPRESS raced near the back through the turn then made a rail bid in the stretch to improve his position. BUMPER POOL was off the pace through the turn but lacked the late response in the stretch. SEAFARING WILDCAT sprinted to the lead from under pressure then was headed at the quarter pole and tired. MYBESTISYETTOCOME tracked the leaders from three wide and gave way in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Purse 12500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF THREE RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIRTUALLY tracked the leaders to the turn then made a three wide bid to engage the leaders at the five sixteenths pole and took command at the top of the stretch and drew off. UNPLUCKED GEM raced in the middle of the pack through the turn then moved to three wide in upper stretch for a late rally and proved second best. TRULY A MESS shared command to the five sixteenths pole then was over taken at the top of the stretch, fought gamely in the stretch and was a clear third. THE GINGER QUEEN (IRE) raced near the back through the turn, moved out to four wide in upper stretch and passed tiring rivals. NAUGHTY EVELYN shared the command to the five sixteenths pole then started to float out and was checked at the quarter pole and dropped back. T R'S FIRST remained back. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUEZ co-led through the turn then continued to match strides down the stretch with outside rival, drifted out but was able to win the nod. WILLTOBELUCKY co-led through the turn then continued to match strides down the stretch with inside rival, while fighting gamely lost the nod. YHA YHA prompted the pace to the top of the stretch and was no match for the top two. KWIK saved ground throughout to no avail and improved position late. TOMBI was reluctant to load, was off the pace while racing wide throughout and never made a bid. UNBROKEN SONG was off slow and remained back. MORHAWK was always back.
